    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. but if the historical evidence is ambiguous or if the original meaning doesn't account for modern technology or social changes, doesn't that just leave the judge with no choice but to make a policy decision anyway? isn't it also true that different historians can interpret the same period in totally different ways, which makes the whole \"objective standard\" thing feel kind of shaky?",
